title: Introduction to JavaScript
contents: JavaScript is a programming language that enables you to create interactive web pages. It is widely used for client-side development.

title: Exploring React Framework
contents: React is a JavaScript library for building user interfaces. It allows developers to create reusable UI components and efficiently update the UI when data changes.

title: Understanding Node.js
contents: Node.js is a server-side JavaScript runtime environment that allows you to build scalable and high-performance applications. It uses an event-driven, non-blocking I/O model.
